PrecisApproval of the appointment by the Minister of Transport of Bernard A. Roy, of Île-des-Soeurs, Quebec, as a director of the Board of Directors of the Canadian National Railway Company to hold office during pleasure for a term of three years, effective July 1, 1992, in the place of Guy Coulombe, who has resigned.
